Kayode Oyero The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), has reconstituted the Board of the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation for three years, The PUNCH reports. This was contained in a statement on Saturday by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. READ ALSO:Â Midnight fire guts Olaleye market in Somolu, Lagos The decision followed the expiration of the term of the Board members appointed in 2016. Members of the new Board include Mohammed Lawal (North West), Tajudeen Umar (North East), Adamu Attah (North Central), Magnus Abe (South-South), Stephen Dike (South East), and Pius Akinyelure (South West).